The President was so enthusiastically talking over the TV about our successes on the world stage, friendship with Nata and our imminent victory over our evil neighbor, that we also put on a helmet over our ears from a saucepan, a bulletproof vest from a mother-in-law bra, lead lace underpants from second-hand and went to buy a piano from LuAZ. We will learn the March of the Winners No. 2 in B flat minor from Chopin.